					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6077738#post-4383999</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6077738/scp-3671#post-4383999</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 01 Oct 2019 19:56:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>SteeredAxe</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5380792</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I would have liked at least an implication about how long this box has been in custody of the foundation. I always feel weary about the anomalies that foundation workers are given free access to and think the foundation would have a vetting process that would take at least a few months before they decide their workers can freely use it. Part of me somewhat gets the impression that it was only around for a few days before the negative quirks started showing.</p> <p>I know I am overthinking what is supposed to be a humor SCP so please forgive me. I personally think everything else is fine.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6077738#post-4383683</guid>
				<title>Site Crit Team</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6077738/scp-3671#post-4383683</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 01 Oct 2019 15:58:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ManyMeats</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2104082</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This piece is short, fairly clever, and did make me smile. Having said that, there's one fairly obvious turn that was made and this turn isn't really followed up on in any way that advances the story. The fake-out with the cyanide was nice and took us to the border of sinister but the narrative fell short of punching you.</p> <p>Not every piece has to, and this is well done for what it is. But Given the extremely fast bailout, I cannot +1 this. No vote from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
